ational life or cast such a long shadow, nor has there ever been another show like it. Nachman's compulsively readable history, illustrated with classic photographs and chocked with colorful anecdotes, reanimates The Ed Sullivan Show for a new generation.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 24. Mai 2022) 0aTelevision personalitiesxBiographyxUnited States. 0aTelevision personalitieszUnited StatesvBiography. 7aPERFORMING ARTS / Television / General.2bisacsh  a20th century american popular culture.  aafrican american music.  aamerican popular culture.  aamerican television.  abroadway gossip columnist.  acareer.  adog acts.  aed sullivan.  aelvis presley.  aentertainment industry.  aentertainment.  ajames brown.  ajugglers.  amusic.  amusicians.  anat king cole.  apearl bailey.  arace in america.  aretrospective.  arichard pryor.  ashow business.  atelevision history.  atelevision.  athe beatles.  athe ed sullivan show.  atv variety show.  aunited states of america.  avaudeville.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of California Press Backlist Package 2000-2013z978311069042240uhttps://doi.org/10.1525/978052094486240uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780520944862423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780520944862/original  a978-3-11-069042-2  University of California Press Backlist Package 2000-2013c2000d2013  aEBA_FAO  aEBA_UCA_YUP  aGBV-deGruyter-alles